deck: An ordinary girl with small breasts.
description:
Origin

A regular girl growing up in regular circumstances with a penchant for thinking about breasts a lot.

Creation

Written and drawn by Monica Gallagher.

Major Story Arcs

In the course of her life, Monica views her flat chest as a benefit in ballet, as most ballerinas have smaller breasts. In high school, however, she begins to notice how much bigger other girls seem to be. She gets excited upon hearing that birth control pills will help a girl fill out, but it doesn't seem to work for Monica.

At 16, Monica joins a modeling agency and competes for spots against girls much younger than herself (as they have similar body types). She is hired to do a fashion show in which she must wear transparent clothing. Due to her smaller breasts, the folds of the clothing hide any sensitive parts - unlike the more amply bosomed models.
name: Monica Gallagher
